        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 8:07PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 807 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Sandtown to Morrow to Richardson Park, and moving
southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail, frequent cloud
to ground lightning and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Atlanta, Conyers, Jonesboro, City of South Fulton, East Point,
Stockbridge, Union City, Forest Park, Riverdale, College Park,
Fairburn, Morrow, Hapeville, Lake City, Lithonia, Hartsfield-Jackson
Airport, Grant Park-Zoo Atlanta, Candler-Mcafee, Lakeview Estates,
and Lake Spivey.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
